    <p><strong>How to practice:</strong> For each pattern, create five sentences using vocabulary you already know. Write them down, then try to say them at natural speed. Recording yourself and comparing with native speakers is particularly effective for internalizing word order. Start with patterns 1-5, which cover 80% of basic conversation, then gradually add the more complex patterns.</p>
